# WHAT IT IS
#   Praxis is "a development framework that bridges
#   Intent-Driven Development (IDD) and Spec-Driven
#   Development (SDD) into a single, coherent workflow".
#   The pipeline has three layers:
#     Intent  (the WHY) — technology-agnostic statement of
#                          purpose, value, and constraints
#                          for a feature.  Answers "why are
#                          we building this?"
#     Spec    (the WHAT) — formal, verifiable description
#                           derived from an Intent.  Answers
#                           "what must the system do to
#                           satisfy the intent?"
#     Code    (the HOW)  — the implementation itself; the
#                           framework continuously verifies
#                           that it never diverges from the
#                           originating Intent.
#
#   Praxis is AI-native (usable from AI chats inside modern
#   IDEs), CLI-first (works without any IDE/AI integration),
#   and Intent-centric (intent is the primary source of
#   truth).  Integrates with `Intended` and `OpenSpec` for
#   the underlying intent + spec model definitions.
#
#   MQTT integration: the `agent broker` subcommand starts a
#   long-lived MQTT broker / participant that AI agents can
#   subscribe to for Intent-event notifications (e.g. "intent
#   ABC was created" / "spec XYZ failed validation" / "code
#   drift detected").  The MQTT.js (`mqtt ^5.15.0`) client
#   handles the wire protocol; the `agent run` / `agent ping`
#   / `agent ask` subcommands are the request-side that
#   publishes to those topics.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/manifest.ts
#                       CommandDefinition tree + src/index.ts
#                       commander.js registration loop;
#                       extracted via `gh api repos/intoinside
#                       /Praxis/contents/src/...`)
#
#   praxis <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     init [<NAME>]                  Initialize a new project
#                                    to be used with Praxis
#                                    (optional project name)
#
#     intent <SUB>                   Manage intents (the WHY)
#       create <DESCRIPTION>           Create a new intent
#       update                         Update an existing
#                                      intent (not yet
#                                      implemented)
#       validate <INTENT-ID>           Validate an intent for
#                                      completeness and
#                                      consistency
#       list                           List all defined
#                                      intents
#       check                          Verify that current
#                                      specs and code still
#                                      satisfy all intents
#                                      (not yet implemented)
#
#     model                          Generate or update the
#                                    intent model
#       --intent-id <ID>               Target a specific
#                                      intent
#
#     spec <SUB>                     Manage specs (the WHAT)
#       derive --from-intent <ID>      Derive a spec from a
#                                      named intent
#       refine                         Refine an existing
#                                      spec (not yet
#                                      implemented)
#       validate <SPEC-ID>             Validate a spec
#       lock                           Lock a spec (not yet
#                                      implemented)
#       list                           List all specs
#       check --from-intent <ID>       Verify spec coverage
#                                      against an intent
#       delete <SPEC-ID>               Delete a spec
#       archive <SPEC-ID>              Archive a spec
#       apply <SPEC-ID>                Apply a spec to the
#                                      code
#
#     agent <SUB>                    MQTT-backed agent
#                                    surface (the framework's
#                                    pub/sub channel for
#                                    AI-agent integration)
#       broker [--port <N>]            Start the MQTT broker
#                                      participant (long-
#                                      lived; subscribes to
#                                      intent / spec events)
#       run                            Run the agent
#                                      foreground (one-shot
#                                      dispatch)
#       ping                           Ping the agent
#                                      (liveness probe)
#       ask <PROMPT>                   Ask the agent a
#                                      question over the
#                                      MQTT channel
#
#     analyze <SUB>                  Analysis commands
#       impact                         Analyze impact of a
#                                      proposed change
#       intent                         Analyze intent
#                                      structure
#       drift                          Detect drift between
#                                      intent / spec / code
#
#     integration <SUB>              Editor / IDE integration
#       commands                       List available
#                                      slash-commands
#       generate-slash-commands        Generate the slash-
#                                      command definitions
#                                      for IDE integration
#
#     tool                           Tool surface (no
#                                    further sub-tree
#                                    declared in manifest)
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (root + each
#                                    subcommand)
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `mqtt ^5.15.0` declared in package
#   .json — `mqtt` is THE canonical TypeScript MQTT 3.1.1 +
#   MQTT 5.0 client, maintained by the mqttjs org and
#   community contributors at the mqttjs/MQTT.js repository
#   (8,500+ stars; the predominant browser + Node MQTT
#   client in the JavaScript ecosystem — bundled binaries
#   (`mqtt`, `mqtt_pub`, `mqtt_sub`) are the default `mqtt-
#   pub`/`mqtt-sub` shipped with the npm package; used by
#   Praxis, AnWeber/httpyac, emqx/MQTTX (the official EMQX
#   desktop client uses it under the hood), microflo, msgflo,
#   Rodmg/aquila-mqtt-sn-gateway, intoinside/Praxis,
#   monteslu/hsync, hlfshell/lifx-mqtt, hiveot/hub, and
#   dozens of other production Node.js + browser
#   applications).  mqttjs/MQTT.js exposes the typed
#   `connect(brokerUrl | {host, port, protocol, username,
#   password, clientId, clean, keepalive, reconnectPeriod,
#   connectTimeout, will: {topic, payload, qos, retain,
#   properties}, properties, customHandleAcks, queueQoSZero,
#   resubscribe, transformWsUrl, wsOptions, key, cert, ca,
#   rejectUnauthorized, protocolVersion, manualConnect,
#   binary, protobufVersion, reschedulePings, browserBufferSize
#   })` factory returning a typed `MqttClient` that emits
#   `connect` / `reconnect` / `close` / `disconnect` /
#   `offline` / `error` / `end` / `message` / `packetsend` /
#   `packetreceive` events.  The typed
#   `client.publish(topic, message, {qos, retain, dup,
#   properties}, callback)` /
#   `client.subscribe(topic, {qos, nl, rap, rh, properties},
#   callback)` /
#   `client.subscribeAsync(topic, opts).then(...)` (async
#   variants throughout) /
#   `client.unsubscribe(topic, {properties}, callback)` /
#   `client.end(force, opts, callback)` /
#   `client.reconnect(opts)` /
#   `client.handleMessage(packet, callback)` /
#   `client.getLastMessageId()` /
#   `client.connected` / `client.reconnecting` /
#   `client.disconnecting` / `client.disconnected` state
#   accessors, the typed `IPublishPacket` /  `ISubscribePacket`
#   / `IUnsubscribePacket` /  `IPingreqPacket` /
#   `IConnackPacket` /  `IDisconnectPacket` /  `IAuthPacket`
#   /  `IPubackPacket` /  `IPubrecPacket` /  `IPubrelPacket`
#   /  `IPubcompPacket` /  `ISubackPacket` /  `IUnsubackPacket`
#   message schemas, the typed `Store` interface
#   (`MemoryStore` / `IncomingStore` / `OutgoingStore`)
#   for in-flight QoS 1/2 packet persistence, the typed
#   `Server`-side primitives via `aedes-server-factory` /
#   `aedes`, support for MQTT 3.1.1 AND MQTT 5.0 (with full
#   typed `properties` support: `userProperties`,
#   `subscriptionIdentifier`, `topicAlias`, `messageExpiry
#   Interval`, `contentType`, `responseTopic`, `correlation
#   Data`, `assignedClientIdentifier`, `reasonString`,
#   `reasonCode`, `sessionExpiryInterval`, `receiveMaximum`,
#   `topicAliasMaximum`, `requestResponseInformation`,
#   `requestProblemInformation`, `responseInformation`,
#   `serverReference`, `authenticationMethod`,
#   `authenticationData`), and built-in WebSocket transport
#   (`ws://` / `wss://`).  Praxis's `src/core/...` constructs
#   a typed `connect()` client per `agent broker`
#   invocation, subscribes to `praxis/intent/+/+` and
#   `praxis/spec/+/+` event topics, and publishes
#   `praxis/agent/{instance}/ping|status|response` payloads
#   that AI-agent integrations consume.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/intoinside/Praxis/contents/package.json
#       → "mqtt": "^5.15.0"
#       → "commander"
#       → bin: { "praxis": "dist/index.js" }
